WHERE CLAUSE :
-- It is used to filter the records.
-- Where clause executes after the execution of from clause.
-- Where clause executes in row by row format.
-- In where clause we write filter condition.
-- We can also write multiple condition in where clause these condition must retur boolean values.
-- Where clause specify the criteria that record must be satisfied

# Syntax :

SELECT */ DISTINCT COL_NAME/ EXPRESSION [ALIAS]
FROM TABLE_NAME
WHERE <FILTER_CONDITION>;

# Execution principle :
1. FROM   -->  Fetch table from database (put table under execution).
2. WHERE  -->  Row by row.
3. SELECT -->  Group by group.

1. WAQTD name and sal of empls working in dno 10.
==> SELECT ENAME,SAL
    FROM EMP
    WHERE DEPTNO = 10;


2. WAQTD details of emps getting sal more than 3k.
==> SELECT ENAME,SAL
    FROM EMP
    WHERE sal > 3000;

3. WAQTD annual sal of the empl whose name is smith.
==> SELECT SAL*12 AS "ANNUAL_SAL_SMITH"
    FROM EMP
    WHERE ENAME = 'SMITH';

4. WAQTD details of the empls who r hired after 1st jan 81.
==> SELECT *
    FROM EMP
    WHERE HIREDATE > TO_DATE('01-JAN-1981', 'DD-MON-YYYY');

5. If no of row are more and u are not getting output table properly then try.
